body:
> Verilator Version:

`Verilator 4.0.34`

> Testcase:

```systemverilog
// t_enum_err.v
package pkg;
    typedef enum {
        A = 10,
        B = 20,
        C = 30
    } en_t;
endpackage

package C;
    parameter one = 1;
    parameter two = 2;
endpackage

module t(/*AUTOARG*/);
    initial begin
        if (pkg::C != 10) $stop;
        $write("*-* All Finished *-*\n");
        $finish;
    end
endmodule
```

> After translated by verilator, I met a error like this:

```
%Error: t_enum_err.v:17:12: syntax error, unexpected PACKAGE-IDENTIFIER, expecting TYPE-IDENTIFIER
   17 |   if (pkg::C != 10) $stop;
      |            ^
%Error: Exiting due to 1 error(s)
```

> I think it might be a bug, what's your opinion?
